cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper deals with learning-based 3D reconstruction from RGB images, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves differentiable rendering techniques, which is also relevant to computer graphics (cs.GR). The paper also discusses the use of implicit shape and texture representations, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). Finally, the paper involves the use of depth gradients and multi-view 3D reconstruction, which are topics in neural networks (cs.NE).
